    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - DISASSEMBLY - REAR CASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="24">
        <title>REAR CASE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300605">Figure 5</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300606">Figure 6</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300605" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300605" filename="../figg13/G1300605.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Exploded View of Rear Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1300606" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300606" filename="../figg13/G1300606.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Exploded View of Rear Case Gears</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain lubricant from transmission.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the interlock retaining drive screw. Then remove the gaskets and interlock retainer
                plate,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300607">Figure 7</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300607" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300607" filename="../figg13/G1300607.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Interlock Retainer Plate</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four springs and plungers,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300608">Figure 8</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300608" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300608" filename="../figg13/G1300608.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Springs and Plungers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The backup light switch can be removed if it is going to be replaced,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300609">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300609" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300609" filename="../figg13/G1300609.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Backup Light Switch Removed</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove plunger plug, pusher, spring and plunger. Replace any worn or damaged parts,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300610">Figure 10</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300610" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300610" filename="../figg13/G1300610.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Remove Plunger Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position transmission on end,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300611">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300611" filename="../figg13/G1300611.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Transmission on End</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove mainshaft nut, washer and end yoke or flange. Refer to Exploded View of Rear Case
                Gears illustration.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the output bearing cap and gasket,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300612">Figure 12</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300612" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300612" filename="../figg13/G1300612.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Output Bearing Cap &#38; Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove speedometer signal rear. Refer to illustrationstep 8.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft bearing cap and shims,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300613">Figure 13</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300613" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300613" filename="../figg13/G1300613.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Countershaft Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to pull countershaft out of the rear of housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300614">Figure 14</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300614" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300614" filename="../figg13/G1300614.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Countershaft Out of Rear Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The countershaft bearing is removed with the shaft,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300615">Figure 15</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300615" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300615" filename="../figg13/G1300615.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Countershaft Bearing Removed</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a suitable puller in the case milled slots and remove the mainshaft rear bearing by
                pulling on the bearing snap ring,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300616">Figure 16</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300616" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300616" filename="../figg13/G1300616.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Mainshaft Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars in the slots provided in the rear case. Break the seal,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300617">Figure 17</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300617" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300617" filename="../figg13/G1300617.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Pry Bars to Break Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a chain hoist to remove the rear housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300618">Figure 18</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300618" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300618" filename="../figg13/G1300618.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Rear Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The reverse idler shaft and gear will remain in the housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300619">Figure 19</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300619" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300619" filename="../figg13/G1300619.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Idler Shaft and Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Notice that the low/reverse shift fork support bracket also stays in the housing. This
                bracket should not be removed unless it is broken and is going to be replaced,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300620">Figure 20</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300620" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300620" filename="../figg13/G1300620.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Low/Reverse Shift Fork Support Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap the reverse idler shaft out of the housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300621">Figure 21</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300621" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300621" filename="../figg13/G1300621.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Tap Reverse Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reverse idler gear, gear and bearings, and two thrust washers,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300622">Figure 22</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300622" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300622" filename="../figg13/G1300622.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Continue by removing the thrust washer, reverse gear, and the caged needle bearings,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300623">Figure 23</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300623" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300623" filename="../figg13/G1300623.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Thrust Washer, Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear shift bar support bracket. Lift the low/reverse fork and collar assembly from
                the housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300624">Figure 24</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300624" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300624" filename="../figg13/G1300624.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Rear Shift Bar Support Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear mainshaft,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300625">Figure 25</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300625" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300625" filename="../figg13/G1300625.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Remove Rear Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove low gear speed mainshaft gear from mainshaft, first remove the snap ring,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300626">Figure 26</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300626" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300626" filename="../figg13/G1300626.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Low Gear Speed Mainshaft Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the thrust washer and lock ball (arrow) next,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300627">Figure 27</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300627" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300627" filename="../figg13/G1300627.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Thrust Washer and Lock Ball</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove low gear and the bearing from the shaft. The clutch gear is a part of the shaft,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300628">Figure 28</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300628" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300628" filename="../figg13/G1300628.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Low Gear and Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
